summary: So Sophia The Robot reviewed some Robots from Pop Culture in a recent BuzzFeed Video and she had that one question that really...
question: So Sophia The Robot reviewed some Robots from Pop Culture in a recent BuzzFeed Video and she had that one question that really stuck with me: why do people assume that R2D2 & C3PO are boys and not girls? And I gotta admit I've never thought about it... What are your thoughts on that? 🤔
answer:
!! :O

Ok ill be honest i never really thought about this before but 2 things come to mind

  • People s tendency to think anything without a gender (a robot… plant.. Cartoon characters ldk) as a Man by default… A white man to be more specific.. Ofc they’ll be boys! Aka good old Patriarchy
  • Also the actors who played then were male 🤔 i think? Though it doesn’t show in the films i think this d affect how people would think them…

This is an interesting question tho !!! What’s your opinion?

blog.name: mandowords
blog.title: Miit'alor
blog.description: I am a descriptivist linguist for the Mando'a language. I show what it can do, not what it MUST do. This is a place for discussion about Mando'a, and Mandalorian society and culture. Feel free to use the head cannons from this blog (or reblogged from others) in your RP or writing. All words and descriptions are taken from the mandoa.org Mandalorian Dictionary. Want to support this blog? Buy me a Kofi? OR buy some Mando'a themed items? Visit our Discord? Blog icon by Rina
